01:05:40,259 --> 01:05:42,145
You look like my son.

521
01:05:43,321 --> 01:05:44,972
I am your son, Dad.

522
01:05:45,643 --> 01:05:47,764
My son's taller than you.

523
01:06:03,506 --> 01:06:04,507
Elise

524
01:07:09,682 --> 01:07:11,097
Someone just came in.

525
01:07:12,960 --> 01:07:16,260
If I could at least
move my fingers.

526
01:07:17,480 --> 01:07:18,895
Or my eyes.

527
01:07:20,578 --> 01:07:22,464
Do you think he can hear us?

528
01:07:23,202 --> 01:07:25,064
Have you seen any reaction?

529
01:07:25,089 --> 01:07:26,247
I don't know, but...

530
01:07:26,732 --> 01:07:28,476
I've got a feeling that he can.

531
01:07:28,501 --> 01:07:29,766
Who's there?

532
01:07:29,900 --> 01:07:31,196
What am I doing here?

533
01:07:31,722 --> 01:07:34,343
If you can hear me,
move your fingers.

534
01:07:34,368 --> 01:07:35,666
I've got to get out of here.

535
01:07:35,782 --> 01:07:38,257
Go back, before the accident.

536
01:08:09,058 --> 01:08:10,826
I believe one thing.

537
01:08:13,098 --> 01:08:18,282
I believe that we should always say
"I love you" to the people we love.

538
01:08:25,802 --> 01:08:27,098
I love you.

539
01:08:34,950 --> 01:08:38,485
Nemo... we shouldn't.

540
01:08:40,118 --> 01:08:41,414
I love Stefano.

541
01:08:43,053 --> 01:08:43,853
What?

542
01:08:44,763 --> 01:08:47,238
You saw him
at the party with me.

543
01:08:49,322 --> 01:08:50,973
He doesn't love me.

544
01:08:52,656 --> 01:08:53,316
And so...

545
01:08:53,341 --> 01:08:54,639
I love him anyways.

546
01:08:55,403 --> 01:08:57,288
I can't help myself.

547
01:08:58,110 --> 01:08:59,524
I'm in love with him.

548
01:09:02,325 --> 01:09:03,268
I'm sorry.

549
01:09:16,030 --> 01:09:17,562
Dad, I'm getting married.

550
01:09:17,812 --> 01:09:18,637
Oh!

551
01:09:19,200 --> 01:09:20,969
And who is the lucky lady?

552
01:09:21,312 --> 01:09:22,372
No, it's not that.

553
01:09:23,950 --> 01:09:26,896
I'm gonna marry the first girl
who dances with me tonight.

554
01:10:05,106 --> 01:10:06,521
Thanks, Nemo.

555
01:10:43,788 --> 01:10:45,085
Nemo.

556
01:10:50,924 --> 01:10:55,048
On that day, I would make
a lot of foolish decisions.

557
01:10:56,340 --> 01:10:59,734
One, I will never
leave anything to chance again.

558
01:10:59,759 --> 01:11:02,577
Two, I will marry the girl
on my motorcycle.

559
01:11:03,086 --> 01:11:04,972
Three, I'll be rich.

560
01:11:05,176 --> 01:11:06,944
Four, we'll have a house.

561
01:11:07,338 --> 01:11:08,582
A big house!

562
01:11:08,607 --> 01:11:10,826
Painted yellow, with a garden,

563
01:11:10,851 --> 01:11:13,265
and two children,
Paul and Michael.

564
01:11:13,290 --> 01:11:16,877
Five, I'll have a convertible--
A red convertible.

565
01:11:16,902 --> 01:11:19,341
And a swimming pool.
I'll learn to swim.

566
01:11:19,486 --> 01:11:23,492
Six, I will not stop
until I've succeeded.

567
01:11:44,674 --> 01:11:45,970
Daddy?

568
01:11:48,206 --> 01:11:49,385
Daddy?

569
01:11:53,621 --> 01:11:55,625
Paul, don't wake your father.

570
01:11:56,524 --> 01:11:57,584
Elise?

571
01:11:58,153 --> 01:11:59,921
It's me, Jean.

572
01:12:02,440 --> 01:12:03,737
Who is Elise?

573
01:12:07,632 --> 01:12:09,517
I don't know
anyone called Elise.

574
01:12:10,221 --> 01:12:12,107
Go back and play Paul.

575
01:12:14,875 --> 01:12:17,586
Nemo, do I matter to you?

576
01:12:21,364 --> 01:12:22,307
I just...

577
01:12:22,542 --> 01:12:25,133
I just like
to ask you one question.

578
01:12:26,491 --> 01:12:28,495
Did you do it on purpose?

579
01:12:31,483 --> 01:12:34,193
I found this
on the bedside table.

580
01:12:35,229 --> 01:12:39,591
There comes a time in life
when everything seems narrow.

581
01:12:39,616 --> 01:12:44,294
Choices have been made
I can only continue on.

582
01:12:44,604 --> 01:12:47,668
I know myself like
the back of my hand.

583
01:12:48,715 --> 01:12:51,401
I can predict my every reaction.

584
01:12:51,426 --> 01:12:53,033
Everything is predictable.

585
01:12:53,733 --> 01:12:58,541
My life has been cast in cement
with airbags and seatbelts.

586
01:12:58,566 --> 01:13:00,482
I've controlled everything.

587
01:13:00,507 --> 01:13:05,103
I've done everything to reach
this point and now that I'm here,

588
01:13:05,355 --> 01:13:07,477
I'm fucking bored.

589
01:13:09,627 --> 01:13:13,045
The hardest thing is knowing
whether I'm still alive.

590
01:13:20,727 --> 01:13:22,965
It is my handwriting.

591
01:13:24,181 --> 01:13:26,184
I don't remember.

592
01:13:43,780 --> 01:13:44,606
Jean?

593
01:13:48,557 --> 01:13:50,205
What did you say?

594
01:13:53,679 --> 01:13:55,093
I had a weird dream.

595
01:14:15,398 --> 01:14:18,585
Well, it's important for you to understand.

596
01:14:18,610 --> 01:14:22,229
In life things don't always turn out...

597
01:14:22,804 --> 01:14:24,648
as we plan them.

598
01:14:25,371 --> 01:14:27,156
Harry and I thought...

599
01:14:29,676 --> 01:14:31,793
Life isn't what we all think it will be.

600
01:14:32,523 --> 01:14:34,532
What are you talking about?

601
01:14:35,781 --> 01:14:36,961
I don't understand.

602
01:14:38,190 --> 01:14:39,958
Anna knows already.

603
01:14:42,907 --> 01:14:45,501
Harry and I
are going to separate.

604
01:14:46,977 --> 01:14:48,037
What?

605
01:14:49,610 --> 01:14:50,671
Why?

606
01:14:52,568 --> 01:14:56,221
- You have no right!
- Please, you played your part!

607
01:14:56,350 --> 01:14:58,459
I don't know what is going on
between you two

608
01:14:58,484 --> 01:15:00,958
and I don't wanna know.
It's sick!

609
01:15:01,088 --> 01:15:04,012
You're brother and sister,
for God's sake.

610
01:15:04,037 --> 01:15:06,416
We are not brother and sister!

611
01:15:13,126 --> 01:15:14,305
You knew!

612
01:15:15,889 --> 01:15:17,538
And you didn't tell me.

613
01:15:25,344 --> 01:15:26,640
Where are you going?

614
01:15:29,484 --> 01:15:30,899
To New York.

615
01:15:33,146 --> 01:15:35,384
In ten days.

616
01:15:36,924 --> 01:15:39,281
My father found a job there.

617
01:15:49,411 --> 01:15:51,767
Wait for me
near the lighthouse...

618
01:15:52,376 --> 01:15:54,499
every Sunday, okay?

619
01:15:56,251 --> 01:15:58,609
Until we see each other again.

620
01:15:58,714 --> 01:16:00,952
For life, okay?

621
01:16:04,600 --> 01:16:06,486
It's not over.

622
01:16:13,967 --> 01:16:17,621
You're the first and last person
I'll ever love.

623
01:16:19,264 --> 01:16:20,797
Ten days.

624
01:16:22,879 --> 01:16:23,822
That makes...

625
01:16:25,531 --> 01:16:27,180
14 thousand...

626
01:16:28,089 --> 01:16:29,975
400 minutes.

627
01:16:34,032 --> 01:16:36,743
I wish everything
would stop right now.

628
01:16:39,044 --> 01:16:41,403
Things would stay
this way forever.

629
01:16:44,290 --> 01:16:47,118
They say that
if you slow your breathing...

630
01:16:48,289 --> 01:16:50,057
time slows down.

631
01:16:52,120 --> 01:16:53,887
The Hindu say so.

632
01:17:34,743 --> 01:17:39,337
I have to remember the smell
of every part of your body.

633
01:17:48,959 --> 01:17:51,082
We'll meet near the lighthouse.

634
01:18:14,805 --> 01:18:16,809
Anna, it's time to go.

635
01:18:27,202 --> 01:18:28,735
I love you.

636
01:19:12,545 --> 01:19:15,491
Anna!

637
01:19:51,136 --> 01:19:51,961
Anna...

638
01:19:53,141 --> 01:19:54,437
Can you hear me?

639
01:20:17,032 --> 01:20:18,800
We must look to the future.

640
01:20:19,605 --> 01:20:21,608
It will be good to move house.

641
01:20:21,878 --> 01:20:23,174
Have a new life.

642
01:20:24,107 --> 01:20:25,523
Will we have a pool?

643
01:20:26,330 --> 01:20:28,806
You hate water.
You don't even swim.

644
01:20:29,482 --> 01:20:32,436
- You never know what you want.
- You know what I don't want?

645
01:20:32,461 --> 01:20:35,371
So tell me, what is it
you don't want?

646
01:20:37,523 --> 01:20:39,526
I don't want to be like you.

647
01:20:41,995 --> 01:20:43,528
You know nothing about me.

648
01:20:44,881 --> 01:20:46,767
I've always loved pools.

649
01:20:49,045 --> 01:20:50,813
When I'm older,
I'll have a pool.

650
01:21:46,771 --> 01:21:47,950
Anna.

651
01:21:49,475 --> 01:21:50,275
Anna.

652
01:21:52,363 --> 01:21:56,252
I feel like I'll be seeing you
at every street corner.

653
01:22:17,961 --> 01:22:20,437
Sometimes I tell myself...

654
01:22:21,126 --> 01:22:23,720
maybe you live
in the same town I do

655
01:22:24,033 --> 01:22:25,801
and I don't know where.

656
01:22:26,134 --> 01:22:29,316
Maybe you're here, very close.

657
01:22:29,999 --> 01:22:33,417
Nemo, do you hear my voice?

658
01:22:35,495 --> 01:22:36,675
Anna!

659
01:22:38,126 --> 01:22:41,208
After 90 days,
the on board computer

660
01:22:41,233 --> 01:22:43,920
is still maintaining
the passengers' metabolism

661
01:22:43,945 --> 01:22:46,384
at the level
of a hibernating frog.

662
01:23:12,642 --> 01:23:14,827
He'd always been fascinated
by the fact

663
01:23:14,852 --> 01:23:18,294
that certain frogs can spend
the winter completely frozen.

664
01:23:18,319 --> 01:23:20,618
And that
when spring comes comma,

665
01:23:20,643 --> 01:23:24,838
they defrost
and begin living again period.

666
01:23:26,390 --> 01:23:28,512
The on board computer displayed...

667
01:23:28,822 --> 01:23:31,179
"End of hibernation".

668
01:23:45,363 --> 01:23:47,131
<i>Welcome to Mars.</i>

669
01:23:47,636 --> 01:23:52,406
<i>We hope you had a pleasant dream
and a refreshing re-awakening.</i>

670
01:23:52,431 --> 01:23:57,059
<i>Please leave your sleep suits in
your suspended animation cubicles</i>

671
01:23:57,084 --> 01:24:00,467
<i>and make your way
through to the Arrivals lounge.</i>

672
01:24:02,115 --> 01:24:05,366
<i>You will be directed to
the rest and recoveration rooms</i>

673
01:24:05,391 --> 01:24:09,952
<i>to prepare for your first excursion
to the red planet itself.</i>

674
01:24:13,328 --> 01:24:16,033
Probably the worst thing
about being on Mars

675
01:24:16,058 --> 01:24:18,145
is that nothing
will happen there.

676
01:24:18,646 --> 01:24:21,004
Time will seem stole and empty.

677
01:24:22,551 --> 01:24:25,025
That doesn't look
like there's much to do.

678
01:24:25,166 --> 01:24:27,287
I hope I brought enough we took.

679
01:24:55,218 --> 01:24:56,161
Day time.

680
01:24:57,761 --> 01:24:59,058
It's day time.

681
01:25:00,899 --> 01:25:01,842
The sun is out.

682
01:25:03,474 --> 01:25:06,302
It's warmer on the right
than on the left

683
01:25:09,945 --> 01:25:14,541
She's different
from the one this morning.

684
01:25:16,556 --> 01:25:18,441
Not the same perfume.

685
01:25:20,778 --> 01:25:22,781
Her hands are soft.

686
01:25:25,061 --> 01:25:26,240
Elise.

687
01:25:28,894 --> 01:25:30,425
Is that Elise?

688
01:25:34,705 --> 01:25:36,945
We sh... We shouldn't.

689
01:25:39,202 --> 01:25:41,323
- I love Stefano.
- Shh.

690
01:25:43,563 --> 01:25:44,859
Don't say anything.

691
01:25:45,962 --> 01:25:47,258
You're the one I love.

692
01:25:49,257 --> 01:25:51,024
You can count on me for Mars.

693
01:25:52,474 --> 01:25:53,652
I promise.

694
01:26:31,609 --> 01:26:33,849
Do you wanna go
for a walk or something?

695
01:26:35,419 --> 01:26:37,540
I don't want anything.

696
01:26:38,507 --> 01:26:39,567
Nothing.

697
01:26:44,439 --> 01:26:47,504
- I'm so horrible.
- No, you're not.

698
01:26:47,712 --> 01:26:51,197
- You're not horrible.
- I can't stand this life anymore.

699
01:26:51,222 --> 01:26:53,813
Think about it, you've got
the most incredible kids.

700
01:26:53,838 --> 01:26:57,457
Stop trying to make me feel better.
I'm actually feeling guiltier.

701
01:27:01,264 --> 01:27:03,622
What's wrong with me?

702
01:27:06,197 --> 01:27:08,319
What is wrong with me?

703
01:27:17,501 --> 01:27:18,561
How's Mom?

704
01:27:19,533 --> 01:27:22,126
She's just a little tired.
She's sleeping.

705
01:27:22,285 --> 01:27:26,765
- She's always tired.
- Yeah, she's always tired.

706
01:27:28,127 --> 01:27:29,423
Is she depressed?

707
01:27:30,117 --> 01:27:31,768
Well, she has ups and downs.

708
01:27:32,493 --> 01:27:33,674
I don't know about you,

709
01:27:33,699 --> 01:27:35,718
but next time Mom
has one of her meltdowns,

710
01:27:35,743 --> 01:27:37,594
I'm gonna go
live somewhere else.

711
01:27:42,718 --> 01:27:46,725
So... who has a joke?

712
01:27:48,157 --> 01:27:48,957
Anybody?

713
01:27:50,862 --> 01:27:51,805
I do.

714
01:27:52,574 --> 01:27:57,406
What's green, small
and goes up and down?

715
01:27:58,057 --> 01:27:59,794
A pea in an elevator.

716
01:27:59,819 --> 01:28:03,438
It's not funny.
Old people humor.

717
01:28:05,370 --> 01:28:06,549
Are you gonna be okay?

718
01:28:06,913 --> 01:28:10,685
Of course. Not 'cause Mom's
not okay that I'm not okay.

719
01:28:30,336 --> 01:28:32,222
I can't stand it anymore.

720
01:28:32,744 --> 01:28:36,278
- That noise...
- I'll ask them to keep it down.

721
01:28:37,477 --> 01:28:39,715
But it is Joyce's birthday.

722
01:28:42,991 --> 01:28:44,640
What kind of mother am I?

723
01:28:48,113 --> 01:28:49,056
I gotta get up.

724
01:29:12,850 --> 01:29:14,384
- Are you having a good time?
- Yeah.

725
01:29:14,409 --> 01:29:15,809
Can I tell you one thing?

726
01:29:15,834 --> 01:29:18,014
You're not allowed to be partying
and not have a good time.

727
01:29:18,039 --> 01:29:18,583
It doesn't work that way.

728
01:29:18,608 --> 01:29:20,105
- I know...
- And you know what, Tess?

729
01:29:20,130 --> 01:29:21,637
You look beautiful.

730
01:29:21,662 --> 01:29:23,543
Beautiful, beautiful, beautiful...

731
01:29:23,568 --> 01:29:25,311
But your friends aren't
dancing enough...

732
01:29:25,336 --> 01:29:28,165
And your mother has to
take care of the situation!

733
01:29:29,153 --> 01:29:30,214
Dancing!

734
01:29:32,699 --> 01:29:33,877
You, over there!

735
01:29:48,304 --> 01:29:50,072
Oh, oh!
This makes me like...

736
01:29:51,576 --> 01:29:52,755
Like a dog!

737
01:30:03,063 --> 01:30:06,009
Now let's get ready.
Take one... two... three!

738
01:30:28,165 --> 01:30:30,285
It was a nice day.

739
01:30:32,819 --> 01:30:35,058
Nicest in a long time.

740
01:30:40,508 --> 01:30:42,369
Okey-dokey.

741
01:30:42,394 --> 01:30:43,839
- Ready?
- Bye, Dad.

742
01:30:44,882 --> 01:30:46,979
Bye. Bye.

743
01:30:47,004 --> 01:30:48,291
- Have fun.
- Bye, Dad.

744
01:30:49,529 --> 01:30:50,472
Bye-bye!

745
01:32:11,132 --> 01:32:12,486
I'm leaving!

746
01:32:12,511 --> 01:32:14,655
I'm leaving! I'm leaving!

747
01:32:42,298 --> 01:32:43,445
Everything will be OK.

748
01:32:44,806 --> 01:32:46,264
That will be all right. Come on.

749
01:32:57,676 --> 01:32:59,294
Do you love me?

750
01:33:01,180 --> 01:33:03,447
I could not live without you.

751
01:36:13,803 --> 01:36:15,884
There is no life without you.

752
01:36:21,698 --> 01:36:23,230
Go slowly.

753
01:36:26,409 --> 01:36:28,294
I have to get used to it.

754
01:36:32,411 --> 01:36:37,949
I talked to you so much when you
weren't there. It's so strange for me...

755
01:36:38,250 --> 01:36:40,253
to talk to you for real.

756
01:36:57,701 --> 01:36:59,704
I need some time, Nemo.

757
01:37:02,396 --> 01:37:04,518
When we were separated at 15,

758
01:37:04,690 --> 01:37:07,758
I said I would never love
anyone else.

759
01:37:07,783 --> 01:37:08,583
Ever.

760
01:37:10,005 --> 01:37:11,891
I would never become attached.

761
01:37:12,473 --> 01:37:14,594
I'd never see you put anywhere.

762
01:37:14,918 --> 01:37:17,039
I'd have nothing for myself.

763
01:37:20,213 --> 01:37:23,985
I decided
I would pretend to be alive.

764
01:37:28,990 --> 01:37:31,228
And this is
what I've been waiting for.

765
01:37:31,909 --> 01:37:33,912
All this time...

766
01:37:35,931 --> 01:37:40,999
Renouncing all possible lives,
for one only...

767
01:37:42,101 --> 01:37:43,161
With you.

768
01:37:53,198 --> 01:37:54,957
But I'm not used to it anymore.

769
01:37:56,710 --> 01:38:00,537
You know... love... I mean.

770
01:38:04,413 --> 01:38:06,521
I'm afraid of losing you again,

771
01:38:07,139 --> 01:38:09,775
I'm afraid of having to do
without you again

772
01:38:10,201 --> 01:38:11,001
I...

773
01:38:11,757 --> 01:38:13,354
I'm terrified of that.

774
01:38:18,768 --> 01:38:20,455
We need to take some time

775
01:38:21,961 --> 01:38:24,295
And, when will I see you again?

776
01:38:31,783 --> 01:38:33,308
Call me at this number

777
01:38:37,088 --> 01:38:38,218
in two days

778
01:38:42,577 --> 01:38:44,248
I'll meet you at the lighthouse.

779
01:39:27,623 --> 01:39:30,568
You know why I lost Anna?

780
01:39:32,199 --> 01:39:34,673
Because two months earlier

781
01:39:34,970 --> 01:39:38,358
An unemployed Brazilian boiled an egg

782
01:39:44,129 --> 01:39:48,177
The heat created
a micro-climate in the room

783
01:39:48,926 --> 01:39:51,437
slight difference of temperature.

784
01:39:54,373 --> 01:39:58,386
And heavy rain, two months later
on the other side of the world

785
01:40:00,286 --> 01:40:05,519
that Brazilian boiled an egg
instead of being at work

786
01:40:05,927 --> 01:40:08,586
He would have lost his job
in a clothing factory

